					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A very good piece- it really manages to build up an atmosphere of mystery, paranoia and terror without ever revealing too much; an excellent example of implied fear. We never see the killer but the particular way the anomaly works is thematically and narratively resonant, and it overall ends up being excellent horror. +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
