					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11710980#post-4249004</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11710980/scp-4534#post-4249004</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 14 May 2019 17:23:20 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a very disturbing description of a person who clearly has an unhealthy obsession with women, combined with the use of their anomalous properties to facilitate this. The ending especially caught me off guard, and was executed fairly well. +1</p> <p>That said, I found the tone rather weak throughout, and I feel the piece could be greatly improved by going over it in detail.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>standard safe-class</p> </blockquote> <p>Safe-class</p> <blockquote> <p>An investigation into the whereabouts of PoI-4534, to prevent further abductions and the spread of SCP-4534 instances, is ongoing.</p> </blockquote> <p>Placing the &quot;is ongoing&quot; after the comma is awkward. I would either scrap the appositive or move it to the end where commas aren't needed.</p> <blockquote> <p>is to be treated as a new SCP-4534 instance.</p> </blockquote> <p>is a new SCP-4534 instance.</p> <blockquote> <p>12.6.2018</p> </blockquote> <p>This date is ambiguous: the reader doesn't have a way of knowing whether you're using the US-style MM/DD/YYYY or European-style DD/MM/YYYY. Instead all of the dates should use the international ISO-8601 standard: YYYY/MM/DD.</p> <blockquote> <p>A tooth of the woman was also found under the toilet.</p> </blockquote> <p>I may be wrong, but I don't think you can determine sex from just a tooth. It also may be more creepy if it was just described as &quot;an unidentified tooth&quot;.</p> <blockquote> <p>A Foundation asset reported the anomaly to the Foundation.</p> </blockquote> <p>Probably could be better worded to avoid saying &quot;Foundation&quot; twice.</p> <blockquote> <p>semen fluid on SCP-4534-54</p> </blockquote> <p>Should be &quot;seminal fluid&quot; or just &quot;semen&quot;.</p> <blockquote> <p>Level 3 priority</p> </blockquote> <p>Level-3</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
